original: Anderbjörk, Jan Erik, landsantikvarie, Växjö, f. 12/4/10 i Stockholm av rektor Lars Gabriel Andersson o. Tyra Björklund. G. 36 m. Birgit Löf-ström. Barn: Karin Ingrid f. 37, Hans Erik 42. — Studiex. v. Lidingö lärov. 28, fil. kand. v. Sthlms högsk. 32. Delt. i arkeol. grävn:exp. i Litauen 31, Ostpreussen 32, museistud. i Tyskl., Ung., Danm., Norge, Finl. Stud :res. t. Afrika 34-35. Inneh. museitjänster i Sthlm, Kalm., Karlskrona, landsantikvarie i Växjö fr. 40. Skr.: upps. i facktidskr. Hobbies: skytte, foto.
translated: Anderbjörk, Jan Erik, provincial antiquarian, Växjö, b. 12/4/10 in Stockholm to principal Lars Gabriel Andersson and Tyra Björklund. Married to Birgit Löfström since 1936, with two children: Karin Ingrid b. 1937 and Hans Erik b. 1942. He studied at Lidingö High School and graduated from Stockholm University with a Bachelor of Arts in 1932. He participated in archaeological excavations in Lithuania in 1931 and East Prussia in 1932. He studied at museums in Germany, Hungary, Denmark, Norway, and Finland. He conducted research trips to Africa from 1934-1935. He has held museum positions in Stockholm, Kalmar, and Karlskrona, and has served as a provincial antiquarian in Växjö since 1940. He has written articles for professional journals and his hobbies include shooting and photography.
